1. *Itko* je mogao vidjeti da je on bio tužan. (Anyone could see that he was sad.)
2. Rekao sam *itkome* da će biti kasno. (I told someone that it would be late.)
3. *Itko* bi to uradio za svoje prijatelje. (Anyone would do that for their friends.)
4. Nisam ni s *itkim* razgovarao o tome. (I didn't talk to anyone about it.)
5. *Itko* bi se ljutio da mu se to dogodi. (Anyone would be angry if that happened to them.)

Note: "itko" is a word in the Croatian language, which is similar to Serbian. In Serbian, the word for "anyone" is "bilo ko" or "bilo koja osoba".